  "parent": "sla",
  "notes": "Standard Polish. Three sibilant series: alveolar /s z ts dz/, retroflex /ʂ ʐ tʂ dʐ/, alveolo-palatal /ɕ ʑ tɕ dʑ/. Nasal vowels ⟨ą ę⟩ realise as VN sequences before stops. FINAL DEVOICING: Polish obstruents devoice in coda/word-finally. NASAL VOWELS: ą→[ɔ] and ę→[ɛ] word-finally in contemporary Polish (de-nasalization); nasal elsewhere before consonants. Sources: Rubach (1984), Bethin (1992), Gussmann (2007).",
