    "notes": "Polish has regular penultimate stress. Vowel letters ó ą ę mark quality, not stress; ó is a vowel quality letter (historical /oː/ → /u/), NOT a stress marker. Exceptions (some first-person plural verbal forms, loanwords, conditional mood) exist but are rare and not orthographically distinguishable. Source: Rubach & Booij (1985), A Grid Theory of Stress in Polish; Wikipedia: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Polish_phonology"
